MASA-OA: Multiple Object Tracker with Integrated Embedding-Based Optimization
and Occlusion-Aware Variants

This project is a derivative work based on MASA (Matching Anything by Segmenting Anything)
Original MASA project: https://github.com/siyuanliii/masa
Copyright 2024 Siyuan Li

MASA-OA Modifications
Copyright 2025 Gonzalo Carretero, Juan P. Llerena, Luis Usero, Miguel A. Patricio
Applied Artificial Intelligence Group (GIAA) at UC3M
Cognitive Science Research Group at UAH

=================================================================================

MODIFICATIONS MADE TO THE ORIGINAL MASA PROJECT:

The following files have been modified or added for MASA-OA:

Modified Files:
- demo/video_demo_with_text.py
  * Added support for loading ground truth detections from MOTChallenge format files
  * Added command-line arguments for benchmark evaluation
  * Added MOT format output for TrackEval compatibility

- masa/models/tracker/masa_tao_tracker.py
  * Integrated Hungarian algorithm optimization for assignment
  * Added Kalman Filter-based motion estimation
  * Implemented occlusion-aware tracking capabilities

Added Files:
- masa/models/tracker/MASA_OA_KF/kalman_filter.py
  * Kalman Filter implementation for motion estimation

- masa/models/tracker/MASA_OA_KF/track.py
  * Track state management with Kalman Filter integration

- run_benchmark.py
  * Automated batch processing script for benchmark evaluation

- benchmarks/
  * Directory structure and utilities for MOT benchmark evaluation

- evaluation/
  * Directory for storing tracking results and visualizations


